<HEADLINE>
EDUCATION MINISTER VISITS VATICAN CATHOLIC EDUCATION CHIEF
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rome,  Jan. 12 (CNA) 01/13/07  16:10:25 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
Minister of Education Tu Cheng-sheng visited Cardinal Zenon
Grocholewski, prefect of the Congregation for Catholic Education
at the Vatican, for talks Friday on promoting cultural and
educational exchanges between Taiwan and the Holy See.
</P>
<P>
Tu, who arrived in Rome a day earlier on a goodwill visit, called
on Grocholewski in the company of Republic of China Ambassador Tu
Chu-sheng.
</P>
<P>
During their talks, Grocholewski said that he was impressed by
Taiwan's political, economic and cultural advances when he
visited that country in 2003.
</P>
<P>
Grocholewski explained the Holy See's educational system and
concepts and emphasized that the Catholic Church instills the
core values of human rights, world peace, justice and family
values in schools operated by the Holy See all over the world.
</P>
<P>
Tu expressed his admiration for the Catholic Church's
contributions to society and said Taiwan identifies with the Holy
See's educational values.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan's universities  are promoting  research into ancient
civilizations with the aim of bringing further understanding in
this field and Taiwan hopes to cooperate with the Holy See in
this regard, he said. Tu was scheduled to arrive later in Turin
to meet a delegation from Kaohsiung City to solicit support for
the city's bid to host the World Games in 2011.
</P>
